						<summary>

						<p>On stone set up in front of the village <hi rend="italic">chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II.</p>						

						<p>This contains the description of the chiefs of the Sinda family of Erambarage as in other inscriptions of the place (cf. <hi rend="italic">South Indian Inscriptions,</hi> Vol. XI, Part II, No. 155). It seems to register a gift to a Jaina deity. Keḷavāḍi and Narayaṁgal are mentioned. The epigraph is badly worn out and the details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
